<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>BCP Service Agreement</title>
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Libre+Baskerville:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Montserrat:ital,wght@0,100..900;1,100..900&display=swap"
    rel="stylesheet" />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Poppins" rel="stylesheet" />
  <style>
    body {
      font-size: 11pt;
      color: #000;
      padding-top: 40px;
      line-height: 1.2;
      font-family: "Aptos", "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
      padding: 8px;
      max-width: 100%;
      background-color: #fff;
      text-align: justify;
    }

    h1,
    h2,
    h3,
    h3,
    h3,
    h5 {
      text-align: left;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    p {
      text-align: justify;
    }

    li {
      text-align: justify;
    }

    div {
      text-align: justify;
    }

    .heading {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: start;
      gap: 14px;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 4px 0;
      color: #801423;
    }

    .main-heading-number {
      font-size: 20px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #801423;
      width: 20px;
    }

    .main-heading-text {
      font-size: 20px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #801423;
      width: 100%;
    }

    .subheading {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: start;
      gap: 14px;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 5px 0;
    }

    .subheading-number {
      font-size: 18px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #072c49;
      width: 40px;
    }

    .subheading-text {
      font-size: 18px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #072c49;
      width: 100%;
    }

    .paragraph {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: start;
      /* padding: 5px 0; */
      gap: 14px;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .paragraph-number {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: black;
      width: 40px;
    }

    .paragraph-text {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: black;
      width: 100%;
    }

    .sub-subheading {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: start;
      gap: 14px;
      align-items: center;
      margin-top: 5px;
    }

    .sub-subheading-number {
      font-size: 16px;
      color: black;
      font-weight: 700;
      width: 40px;
    }

    .sub-subheading-text {
      font-size: 16px;
      color: black;
      font-weight: 700;
      width: 100%;
    }

    .sub-subheading-para {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: start;
      gap: 14px;
      align-items: start;
      margin-top: 5px;
    }

    .sub-subheading-para-number {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: black;
      width: 40px;
    }

    .sub-subheading-para-text {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: black;
      width: 100%;
    }

    .list {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: start;
      gap: 14px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .list-ul {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: black;
      /* width: 50px; */
      margin-left: 50px;
      margin-top: 5px;
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    li {
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }

    /* Prevent headings from being left at the bottom of a page */
    .heading,
    .subheading,
    .sub-subheading,
    .sub-subheading-para {
      page-break-after: avoid;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    /* Prevent list and paragraph blocks from breaking mid-content */
    /* .list-ul, */
    .list,
    .paragraph,
    .paragraph-text,
    .sub-subheading-para-text {
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center">
    <img src="<%= logoPath %>" alt="BookCraft Logo" style="height: 90px; margin-top: 30px" />
  </div>
  <br />
  <h1 style="text-align: center; width: 100%; margin-top: 20px">
    SERVICE AGREEMENT
  </h1>
  <br />

  This <span style="font-weight: 600">Service Agreement</span> (the
  "Agreement") is made and entered into as of <%= effectiveDate %> (the
    "Effective Date") by and between:

    <br />
    <br />

    <span style="font-weight: 600">BookCraft Publishers,</span> a company
    registered
    <span style="font-weight: 600">(Incorporation Number 805711782)</span>
    under the laws of Texas, USA, having its principal office at 12828 Willow
    Centre Dr Ste D # 225, Houston, Texas, USA 77066, Phone: 888 905 0868, and
    Email: info@bookcraftpublishers.com (hereinafter individually referred to as
    “BookCraft”); and

    <br />
    <br />

    <p style="margin-top: -10px"></p>
    <p style="margin-top: -10px">
      <%= abbreviation %>
        <%= clientFullName %>, Phone: <%= clientPhone %>,
            Email: <%= clientEmail %>, and a resident of <%= clientLocation %>
                (hereinafter referred to individually as the "Client").

                <br />
                <br />

                BookCraft and the Client shall collectively be referred to as the
                “Parties.”
    </p>

    <div class="heading">
      <div class="main-heading-number">1.</div>
      <div class="main-heading-text">SCOPE OF AGREEMENT</div>
    </div>
    <div class="subheading">
      <div class="subheading-number">1.1</div>
      <div class="subheading-text">Purpose</div>
    </div>
    <div class="paragraph">
      <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
      <div class="paragraph-text">
        This Agreement outlines the engagement between
        <span style="font-weight: 600">BookCraft</span> and the
        <span style="font-weight: 600">Client</span>
        for specific professional book-related services as specified in Clause
        1.2 below. The Client acknowledges that BookCraft is an independent
        service provider and not a traditional publisher, meaning the Client
        retains ownership of their book and is responsible for making all final
        decisions regarding their project.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="subheading">
      <div class="subheading-number">1.2</div>
      <div class="subheading-text">Customizable Service Offerings</div>
    </div>
    <div class="paragraph">
      <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
      <div class="paragraph-text">
        The Client has selected the following service(s) offered by BookCraft:
      </div>
    </div>
    <% filteredServices.forEach((service, index)=> { %>
      <div class="sub-subheading">
        <div class="sub-subheading-number">
          <%= `1.2.${index + 1}` %>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-text">
          <%= service.title %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="list">
        <!-- <div class="list-number"></div> -->
        <ul class="list-ul">
          <% service.items.forEach(item=> { %> <% if (item.title && item.description) { %>
              <li><strong>
                  <%= item.title %>
                </strong> – <%= item.description %>
              </li>
              <% } %>
                <% }) %>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <% }) %>

        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">1.3</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">
            Service Provider&#x27;s Responsibilities
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="paragraph">
          <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
          <div class="paragraph-text">BookCraft agrees to:</div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>
              Deliver all selected services in accordance with industry standards
              and agreed timelines.
            </li>
            <li>
              Communicate regular updates regarding project milestones, approvals,
              and revisions.
            </li>
            <li>
              Ensure data security and confidentiality for all materials provided by
              the Client.
            </li>
            <li>
              Provide professional expertise and guidance to help clients achieve
              their publishing goals.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">1.4</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">Client&#x27;s Responsibilities</div>
        </div>
        <div class="paragraph">
          <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
          <div class="paragraph-text">The Client agrees to:</div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>
              Provide all required materials (manuscript, images, descriptions,
              approvals) in a timely manner.
            </li>
            <li>
              Be responsive and available for necessary feedback, approvals, and
              communication.
            </li>
            <li>
              Be aware that revisions exceeding the agreed-upon limits may incur
              additional costs.
            </li>
            <li>
              Acknowledge that BookCraft does not guarantee book sales, rankings, or
              reader engagement, as success depends on various external factors.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">1.5</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">Modifications to Scope</div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">1.5.1</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            The Client may request additional services or modifications to the
            originally selected services,subject to approval by BookCraft.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">1.5.2</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            If modifications require significant additional effort or time,
            BookCraft reserves the right to adjust project timelines and fees
            accordingly.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">1.6</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">Acceptance of Deliverables</div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">1.6.1</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            The Client shall review all deliverables within seven (7) business days
            of receipt and either approve them or submit revision requests.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">1.6.2</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            The deliverables will be deemed accepted if no revisions are requested
            within the specified period.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">1.6.3</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            The Client acknowledges that excessive or unreasonable revision requests
            may incur additional charges.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="heading">
          <div class="main-heading-number">2.</div>
          <div class="main-heading-text">TERM AND TERMINATION</div>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">2.1</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">Term of Agreement</div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">2.1.1</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            This Agreement commences on the Effective Date. It shall remain in
            effect until all services are completed unless terminated earlier in
            accordance with this Agreement.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">2.1.2</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            For multi-phase projects (e.g., editing followed by publishing and
            marketing), the term may be extended based on project timelines,
            milestones, and client approvals.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">2.1.3</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            If the Client engages BookCraft for ongoing marketing or distribution
            services, this Agreement shall remain in effect until either party
            provides written notice of termination in accordance with the conditions
            set forth below.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">2.2</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">
            Service Milestones &amp; Completion Timeframes
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">2.2.1</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            The estimated duration for completing the services shall be defined
            based on the selected services.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">2.2.2</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            Delays due to late Client responses, incomplete materials, or additional
            revision requests may impact the timeline. BookCraft shall not be liable
            for such delays.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">2.3</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">Termination by Either Party</div>
        </div>
        <div class="paragraph">
          <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
          <div class="paragraph-text">
            Either party may terminate this Agreement prior to project completion
            under the following conditions:
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading">
          <div class="sub-subheading-number">2.3.1</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-text">Termination for Convenience</div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>
              Either the Client or BookCraft may terminate this Agreement for any
              reason by providing fourteen (14) days&#x27; written notice.
            </li>
            <li>
              If termination occurs before the completion of services, the Client
              shall compensate BookCraft for all work completed or rendered up to
              the termination date and any non-refundable expenses incurred on
              behalf of the Client.
            </li>
            <li>
              For marketing and promotion contracts or recurring services, a 30-day
              notice period is required before cancellation.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading">
          <div class="sub-subheading-number">2.3.2</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-text">Termination for Material Breach</div>
        </div>
        <div class="paragraph" style="margin-top: 5px">
          <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
          <div class="paragraph-text">
            If either party breaches a material term of this Agreement and fails to
            remedy such breach within seven (7) days after receiving a written
            notice of default, the non-breaching party may terminate this Agreement
            immediately.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sub-subheading">
          <div class="sub-subheading-number">2.3.3</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-text">
            A material breach includes but is not limited to:
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>Failure to make payments.</li>
            <li>
              Failure to deliver required materials (manuscript, approvals) within
              agreed timelines.
            </li>
            <li>Unauthorized use or disclosure of confidential information.</li>
            <li>
              Refusal to comply with intellectual property and copyright
              obligations.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">2.4</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">Effect of Termination</div>
        </div>
        <div class="paragraph">
          <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
          <div class="paragraph-text">
            Upon termination, the following obligations shall apply:
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading">
          <div class="sub-subheading-number">2.4.1</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-text">Payment Obligations</div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>
              The Client shall pay for all services rendered up to the termination
              date, including any non-refundable deposits or expenses incurred.
            </li>
            <li>
              If termination occurs after partial completion of work, the Client
              shall not be entitled to a refund for services already provided.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading">
          <div class="sub-subheading-number">2.4.2</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-text">Transfer of Work Completed:</div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>
              The Client shall receive all work completed up to the termination
              date, provided that all outstanding balances are settled.
            </li>
            <li>
              If full payment is not received, BookCraft retains the right to
              withhold deliverables until payment is made.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading">
          <div class="sub-subheading-number">2.4.3</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-text">Return of Client Materials:</div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>
              BookCraft shall return any original Client-provided materials upon
              request.
            </li>
            <li>
              Digital files will be retained thirty (30) days after termination,
              after which they may be deleted from BookCraft’s systems.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading">
          <div class="sub-subheading-number">2.4.4</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-text">Survival of Certain Clauses:</div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>
              The confidentiality obligations under Clause 5 (Confidentiality &amp;
              Data Protection) shall remain in effect even after termination.
            </li>
            <li>
              Any intellectual property rights granted under Clause 4 (Intellectual
              Property Rights) shall survive in accordance with this Agreement.
            </li>
            <li>
              The Client shall remain responsible for any outstanding payments due
              under the Contract.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">2.5</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">
            BookCraft’s Right to Termination for Non-Payment or Uncooperative
            Conduct
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading">
          <div class="sub-subheading-number">2.5.1</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-text">Non-Payment Termination:</div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>
              If the Client fails to make a scheduled payment within seven (7) days
              of the due date, BookCraft reserves the right to suspend or terminate
              services until payment is received.
            </li>
            <li>
              If the Client remains nonresponsive regarding overdue payments,
              BookCraft may escalate collection efforts, including using a
              collection agency or taking legal action.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading">
          <div class="sub-subheading-number">2.5.2</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-text">Uncooperative or Abusive Conduct:</div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>
              BookCraft reserves the right to terminate this Agreement immediately
              if the Client engages in abusive, harassing, or unprofessional conduct
              toward BookCraft’s staff. This includes but is not limited to:
              <ul>
                <li>Inappropriate or offensive language.</li>
                <li>Repeated failure to provide necessary information.</li>
                <li>
                  Unreasonable or excessive revision requests that exceed
                  agreed-upon limits.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              No refunds shall be issued in such cases, and the Client shall remain
              liable for all work, whether completed or partially rendered.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">2.6</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">
            Effect of Termination on Book Publishing &amp; Distribution
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="paragraph">
          <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
          <div class="paragraph-text">
            For Clients utilizing publishing or distribution services, termination
            will not impact the availability of their book(s) in online
            marketplaces:
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>
              If BookCraft was responsible for eBook distribution or print-on-demand
              setup, the Client may not need to re-register with retailers (e.g.,
              Amazon KDP, IngramSpark, Apple Books) if the service is discontinued.
            </li>
            <li>
              The Client may request a handover of distribution accounts, where
              applicable; however, BookCraft will not be responsible for
              re-establishing the book on new platforms.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">2.7</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">
            Force Majeure &amp; Unforeseen Circumstances
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">2.7.1</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            Neither party shall be held liable for delays or termination due to
            events beyond their control, including but not limited to:
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>Natural disasters (such as floods, earthquakes, and pandemics).</li>
            <li>Government actions or regulatory changes.</li>
            <li>
              Cybersecurity attacks, system failures, or major technical issues.
            </li>
            <li>
              Labor strikes, supply chain disruptions, or publisher shutdowns.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">2.7.2</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            In the event of force majeure, both parties shall make reasonable
            efforts to resume performance as soon as feasible or agree to a mutually
            acceptable resolution.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">2.8</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">Renewal &amp; Continuation of Services</div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">2.8.1</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            For ongoing marketing, distribution, or consultation services, the
            Agreement shall be automatically renewed for an additional one-month
            period unless terminated by either party with written notice at least
            seven (7) days prior to the end of the current term.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading-para">
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-number">2.8.2</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-para-text">
            BookCraft reserves the right to revise service pricing and terms upon
            renewal, subject to the Client&#x27;s approval.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">2.9</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">Reinstatement of Terminated Services</div>
        </div>
        <div class="paragraph">
          <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
          <div class="paragraph-text">
            If the Client wishes to re-engage BookCraft after termination, they must
            submit a written request, and the reinstatement shall be subject to:
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="list">
          <ul class="list-ul">
            <li>A reinstatement fee of $100 (if applicable).</li>
            <li>Payment of any outstanding balances before work resumes.</li>
            <li>New timelines and revised contract terms, if necessary.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="heading">
          <div class="main-heading-number">3.</div>
          <div class="main-heading-text">FEES, PAYMENTS, AND REFUNDS</div>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">3.1</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">Service Fees and Pricing Structure</div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading">
          <div class="sub-subheading-number">3.1.1</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-text">
            Customized Pricing Based on Services Selected
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="paragraph">
          <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
          <div class="paragraph-text">
            The Client agrees to pay BookCraft a total fee of USD <%= finalFee %>
              for the selected services.
              <br />
              <% if (discountPercent> 0) { %> (The original fee was USD <%= totalFee %>, with a discount of <%=
                    discountPercent %>%, resulting in a
                    net payable amount of USD <%= finalFee %>.) <% } %>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="subheading">
          <div class="subheading-number">3.2</div>
          <div class="subheading-text">Payment Terms and Schedule</div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub-subheading">
          <div class="sub-subheading-number">3.2.1</div>
          <div class="sub-subheading-text">
            Payment Schedule Based on Project Phases
          </div>
        </div>
        <% if ( scheduleType==="100% upon signing" || scheduleType==="Percentage + Monthly Installments" ||
          scheduleType==="Fixed Amount + Monthly Installments" ||
          scheduleType==="Advance + Final Payment (linked to service)" || scheduleType==="Milestone-Based Schedule" ) {
          %>
