                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-subheading">
              <div class="sub-subheading-number">9.3.2</div>
              <div class="sub-subheading-text">Preservation of Agreement Integrity</div>
            </div>

            <div class="list">
              <ul class="list-ul">
                <li>
                  The unenforceability of one section or clause does not affect the
                  validity of the entire Agreement.
                </li>
                <li>
                  If a court of law modifies or removes a clause, both parties shall
                  work in good faith to amend the Agreement accordingly.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="subheading">
              <div class="subheading-number">9.4</div>
              <div class="subheading-text">No Waiver of Rights</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-subheading">
              <div class="sub-subheading-number">9.4.1</div>
              <div class="sub-subheading-text">Non-Waiver of Enforcement Rights</div>
            </div>

            <div class="list">
              <ul class="list-ul">
                <li>
                  If either party fails to enforce any provision of this Agreement at
                  any time, it shall not constitute a waiver of that provision or any
                  future rights.
                </li>
                <li>
                  The failure to take immediate legal action for a breach does not
                  eliminate the right to take action in the future.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-subheading">
              <div class="sub-subheading-number">9.4.2</div>
              <div class="sub-subheading-text">Written Waivers Only</div>
            </div>

            <div class="list">
              <ul class="list-ul">
                <li>
                  Any waiver of rights or obligations must be documented in writing and
                  signed by the party waiving the rights or obligations.
                </li>
                <li>
                  A written waiver shall only apply to the specific instance mentioned
                  and shall not create a precedent for future waivers.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="subheading">
              <div class="subheading-number">9.5</div>
              <div class="subheading-text">Assignment and Transfer of Agreement</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-subheading">
              <div class="sub-subheading-number">9.5.1</div>
              <div class="sub-subheading-text">Restrictions on Assignments</div>
            </div>

            <div class="list">
              <ul class="list-ul">
                <li>
                  The Client shall not assign, transfer, or delegate their rights or
                  obligations under this Agreement to any other party without the prior
                  written consent of the Service Provider.
                </li>
                <li>
                  The Service Provider may assign or subcontract aspects of the work
                  (e.g., hiring freelance editors, designers, or marketers) but remains
                  responsible for delivering the agreed services.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-subheading">
              <div class="sub-subheading-number">9.5.2</div>
              <div class="sub-subheading-text">Successors and Assigns</div>
            </div>

            <div class="list">
              <ul class="list-ul">
                <li>
                  This Agreement shall be binding upon and benefit both parties, their
                  heirs, successors, and legal assigns.
                </li>
                <li>
                  If the Service Provider undergoes a merger, acquisition, or business
                  restructuring, this Agreement shall remain valid and enforceable.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="subheading">
              <div class="subheading-number">9.6</div>
              <div class="subheading-text">Survival of Terms After Termination</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-subheading">
              <div class="sub-subheading-number">9.6.1</div>
              <div class="sub-subheading-text">Clauses That Remain in Effect</div>
            </div>

            <div class="paragraph">
              <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
              <div class="paragraph-text">
                Certain provisions of this Agreement shall remain enforceable even after
                the termination or completion of the services, including:
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="list">
              <ul class="list-ul">
                <li>Intellectual Property Rights (Clause 4).</li>
                <li>Confidentiality and Non-Disclosure Obligations (Clause 5).</li>
                <li>Liability and Indemnification (Clause 7).</li>
                <li>Governing Law and Dispute Resolution (Clause 8).</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-subheading">
              <div class="sub-subheading-number">9.6.2</div>
              <div class="sub-subheading-text">Final Obligations After Termination</div>
            </div>

            <div class="paragraph">
              <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
              <div class="paragraph-text">
                Upon termination, the Client remains responsible for:
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="list">
              <ul class="list-ul">
                <li>Settling outstanding invoices.</li>
                <li>
                  Returning confidential materials or proprietary assets belonging to
                  the Service Provider.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Ceasing any further use of licensed designs, marketing materials, or
                  Service Provider property unless granted ongoing rights.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="subheading">
              <div class="subheading-number">9.7</div>
              <div class="subheading-text">Headings and Interpretation</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-subheading">
              <div class="sub-subheading-number">9.7.1</div>
              <div class="subheading-text">Use of Headings for Reference</div>
            </div>

            <div class="list">
              <ul class="list-ul">
                <li>
                  The section headings and subheadings in this Agreement are for
                  reference purposes only and shall not affect the interpretation of the
                  clauses.
                </li>
                <li>
                  In the event of ambiguity, the entire clause shall be reviewed in full
                  to determine its intended meaning.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-subheading">
              <div class="sub-subheading-number">9.7.2</div>
              <div class="sub-subheading-text">Interpretation in Favor of Clarity</div>
            </div>

            <div class="paragraph">
              <div class="paragraph-number"></div>
              <div class="paragraph-text">
                Any disputes related to the interpretation of this Agreement shall be
                resolved in favor of:
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="list">
              <ul class="list-ul">
                <li>Ensuring fairness to both parties.</li>
                <li>Preserving the original intent of the Agreement.</li>
                <li>Minimizing unnecessary legal ambiguity.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="subheading">
              <div class="subheading-number">9.8</div>
              <div class="subheading-text">Execution and Counterparts</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-subheading">
              <div class="sub-subheading-number">9.8.1</div>
              <div class="sub-subheading-text">Electronic and Digital Signatures</div>
            </div>

            <div class="list">
              <ul class="list-ul">
                <li>
                  This Agreement may be signed either physically or electronically via a
                  legally recognized electronic signature platform (e.g., DocuSign,
                  Adobe Sign).
                </li>
                <li>
                  Digital signatures shall be deemed valid and enforceable in the same
                  manner as handwritten signatures.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="sub-subheading">
              <div class="sub-subheading-number">9.8.2</div>
              <div class="sub-subheading-text">Signing in Counterparts</div>
            </div>

            <div class="list">
              <ul class="list-ul">
                <li>
                  This Agreement may be executed in multiple counterparts, each of which
                  shall be considered an original; however, all of them together shall
                  constitute one binding Agreement.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="heading">
              <div class="main-heading-number">10.</div>
              <div class="main-heading-text">SIGNATURES &amp; EXECUTION</div>
            </div>
            <p style="font-weight: 700">
              By signing below, both Parties acknowledge that they have read,
              understood, and agreed to the terms and conditions outlined in this
              Agreement.
            </p>

